        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 5:06PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 506 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from near Amsterdam to near Delanson to near Cobleskill.
Movement was east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Shakers, West Richmondville, Glenridge, Hoffmans, West Berne, Harding
Crossing, Willow Glen, Summit, Garrison Manor, Quaker Street,
Princetown, West Fulton, Woodruff Heights, Loudonville, Elnora, Halls
Corner, Grays Corners, Eminence, Hutchinson Crossing, and Clifton
Park Center.

People attending Niska Day 2025 should seek safe shelter immediately!

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 88 between exits 20 and 25.
Interstate 90 between exits 4 and 27.
Interstate 890 between exits 1a and 9.
Interstate 87 between exits 24 and 7, and between exits 8A and 12.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
eastern and east central New York.</instruction>
